{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881413787,"sessionID":"ses_28538c162ffeTvSu32nXKbaKjD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac7ddf0001zFpK3Lpawee0k5","messageID":"msg_d7ac7c4d50018JKcvou9XGqea8","sessionID":"ses_28538c162ffeTvSu32nXKbaKjD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_002b0c0aa41743bda5844f2b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","limit":200,"offset":710},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n710: - [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n711: - [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n712: - [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n713: \n714: ---\n715: \n716: # AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n717: \n718: - **AR ID**: AR-038\n719: - **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n720: - **Language**: Go\n721: - **Size**: L\n722: - **Status**: ST-1 In Progress\n723: \n724: ## 1. Overview\n725: \n726: This document provides technical implementation details for comprehensive Go unit tests in the workloadmanager module. The test suite covers all major components including WorkloadManager service, GC worker, expiration checker, graceful shutdown manager, cleanup manager, and the reconciler.\n727: \n728: ## 2. Architecture Overview\n729: \n730: The `pkg/workloadmanager` module provides resource lifecycle management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources:\n731: \n732: | Component | File | Responsibility |\n733: |-----------|------|----------------|\n734: | WorkloadManager | `service.go` | CRUD operations, sandbox operations |\n735: | GC Worker | `gc.go` | Periodic garbage collection (existing tests: 967 lines) |\n736: | Expiration Checker | `expiration.go` | TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime logic |\n737: | Graceful Manager | `graceful.go` | Connection draining, pre-delete hooks |\n738: | Cleanup Manager | `cleanup.go` | Orphaned resource cleanup |\n739: | K8s Client | `client.go` | Kubernetes client initialization |\n740: | Reconciler | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | AgentRuntime reconciliation |\n741: | Server | `server.go` | HTTP server initialization |\n742: \n743: ### Test File Organization\n744: \n745: ```\n746: pkg/workloadmanager/\n747: ├── service_test.go           # WorkloadManager interface tests\n748: ├── client_test.go            # K8sClient initialization tests  \n749: ├── gc_test.go                # GC worker tests (EXISTING)\n750: ├── expiration_test.go        # Expiration checker tests (EXISTING)\n751: ├── graceful_test.go         # Graceful manager tests\n752: ├── cleanup_test.go          # Cleanup manager tests\n753: ├── delete_test.go           # Delete operation tests\n754: ├── server_test.go           # Server initialization tests\n755: ├── batch_test.go            # Batch operations tests\n756: └── reconciler/\n757:     ├── reconciler_test.go   # Reconciler tests\n758:     └── errors_test.go       # Error handling tests\n759: ```\n760: \n761: ## 3. Data Structures\n762: \n763: ### Core Types (`types.go`)\n764: ```go\n765: type Sandbox struct {\n766:     Name           string\n767:     Namespace      string\n768:     SessionID      string\n769:     State          SandboxState\n770:     CreatedAt      time.Time\n771:     ExpiresAt      *time.Time\n772:     LastActivityAt *time.Time\n773:     Labels         map[string]string\n774:     Annotations    map[string]string\n775: }\n776: \n777: type SandboxState string\n778: const (\n779:     SandboxStateUnknown  SandboxState = \"Unknown\"\n780:     SandboxStatePending  SandboxState = \"Pending\"\n781:     SandboxStateRunning  SandboxState = \"Running\"\n782:     SandboxStateFailed   SandboxState = \"Failed\"\n783:     SandboxStateDeleting SandboxState = \"Deleting\"\n784: )\n785: \n786: type DeleteOptions struct {\n787:     GracePeriodSeconds *int64\n788:     Force              bool\n789:     LabelSelector      string\n790:     Preconditions      *Preconditions\n791: }\n792: ```\n793: \n794: ### Error Types\n795: ```go\n796: var (\n797:     ErrSandboxNotFound    = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n798:     ErrDeletionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion failed\")\n799:     ErrStaleFinalizer     = errors.New(\"stale finalizer\")\n800:     ErrOrphanedResource   = errors.New(\"orphaned resource\")\n801:     ErrResourceNotFound   = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n802:     ErrResourceNotDeleted = errors.New(\"resource not deleted\")\n803: )\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ### Configuration Types\n807: ```go\n808: type GCConfig struct {\n809:     GCEnabled   bool\n810:     GCInterval  time.Duration\n811:     GCBatchSize int\n812: }\n813: \n814: type ExpirationConfig struct {\n815:     TTL         time.Duration\n816:     IdleTimeout time.Duration\n817:     MaxLifetime time.Duration\n818: }\n819: \n820: type ReconcilerConfig struct {\n821:     SyncInterval   time.Duration\n822:     MaxRetries     int\n823:     RetryDelays    time.Duration\n824:     Namespace      string\n825:     EnableMetrics  bool\n826:     Workers        int\n827:     RateLimitBurst int\n828:     RateLimitQPS   float64\n829: }\n830: ```\n831: \n832: ## 4. API Contracts\n833: \n834: ### WorkloadManager Interface (`service.go:15-39`)\n835: ```go\n836: type WorkloadManager interface {\n837:     // AgentRuntime CRUD\n838:     CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n839:     GetAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n840:     ListAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*AgentRuntimeList, error)\n841:     UpdateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n842:     DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) error\n843:     GetAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntimeStatus, error)\n844:     PatchAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, pt, data, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n845:     WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (watch.Interface, error)\n846:     \n847:     // CodeInterpreter CRUD (same method pattern)\n848:     \n849:     // Sandbox operations\n850:     DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, sessionID, opts) error\n851:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, namespace, sessionID) (*Sandbox, error)\n852:     ListSandboxes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*SandboxList, error)\n853:     \n854:     Close() error\n855: }\n856: ```\n857: \n858: ### GC Worker Interface (`gc.go:59-70`)\n859: ```go\n860: type GCWorker struct {\n861:     client            versioned.Interface\n862:     k8sClient         *kubernetes.Clientset\n863:     config            *GCConfig\n864:     stopCh            chan struct{}\n865:     cleanupMgr        *CleanupManager\n866:     expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n867:     stats             GCStats\n868: }\n869: \n870: func (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context)\n871: func (g *GCWorker) Stop()\n872: func (g *GCWorker) IsRunning() bool\n873: func (g *GCWorker) GetConfig() *GCConfig\n874: func (g *GCWorker) GetStats() GCStats\n875: func (g *GCWorker) TriggerGCCycle(ctx) *GCResult\n876: func (g *GCWorker) UpdateConfig(config *GCConfig)\n877: ```\n878: \n879: ### Reconciler Interface (`reconciler/reconciler.go:128-169`)\n880: ```go\n881: type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n882:     client         versioned.Interface\n883:     k8sClient      *workloadmanager.K8sClient\n884:     scheme         *runtime.Scheme\n885:     recorder       record.EventRecorder\n886:     config         *ReconcilerConfig\n887:     metrics        *ReconcilerMetrics\n888: }\n889: \n890: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ReconcileRequest) (ReconcileResult, error)\n891: ```\n892: \n893: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n894: \n895: ### 5.1 Testing Approach\n896: \n897: **Unit Testing Principles:**\n898: 1. Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n899: 2. Mock external Kubernetes clients using fake clientsets\n900: 3. Test both success and error paths comprehensively\n901: 4. Verify state transitions and side effects\n902: 5. Ensure thread-safety for concurrent operations\n903: \n904: **Mock Strategy:**\n905: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake` for typed clients\n906: - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` for Kubernetes clientset\n907: - Custom mock interfaces for complex dependencies\n908: \n909: ### 5.2 Test Utilities\n\n(Showing lines 710-909 of 1081. Use offset=910 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n- [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n\n---\n\n# AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-038\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 In Progress\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for comprehensive Go unit tests in the workloadmanager module. The test suite covers all major components including WorkloadManager service, GC worker, expiration checker, graceful shutdown manager, cleanup manager, and the reconciler.\n\n## 2. Architecture Overview\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775881413768,"end":1775881413785}}}}
