{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881424257,"sessionID":"ses_28538c162ffeTvSu32nXKbaKjD","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac8068a001IX3IiqEMGwXtlB","messageID":"msg_d7ac7fa180015qQDH8XpQdnHld","sessionID":"ses_28538c162ffeTvSu32nXKbaKjD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5e9802f25f8a441b812240f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","limit":100,"offset":310},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n310: | `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n311: | `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n312: | `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n313: | `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: # Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n318: \n319: ## Overview\n320: \n321: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n322: \n323: ## Base Specifications\n324: \n325: - **AR**: AR-038\n326: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n327: - **Language**: Go\n328: - **Size**: L\n329: \n330: ## Reference\n331: \n332: Base spec: client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ## Background\n337: \n338: The workloadmanager module provides workload management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes. It includes:\n339: - WorkloadManager interface for CRUD operations\n340: - GC (Garbage Collection) worker for expired resource cleanup\n341: - Expiration checker for TTL and idle timeout\n342: - Graceful manager for connection draining\n343: - Cleanup manager for orphaned resources\n344: - Batch manager for bulk operations\n345: - HTTP server with REST API endpoints\n346: \n347: ---\n348: \n349: ## Requirements\n350: \n351: ### Feature: CleanupManager Resource Cleanup\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-A — CleanupManager deletes orphaned services\n354: \n355: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n356: - **WHEN** cleanupServices is called with a namespace and owner reference\n357: - **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned service resource strings\n358: - **AND** services with matching owner references should be deleted\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-B — CleanupManager deletes orphaned configmaps\n361: \n362: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n363: - **WHEN** cleanupConfigMaps is called with a namespace and owner reference\n364: - **THEN** it should return a list of cleaned configmap resource strings\n365: - **AND** configmaps with the annotation `agentcube.volcano.sh/auto-delete=true` and matching owner should be deleted\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-C — CleanupManager handles retained PVCs\n368: \n369: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n370: - **WHEN** cleanupPVCs is called with a namespace and owner reference for a PVC with Retain policy\n371: - **THEN** the PVC should not be deleted\n372: - **AND** other PVCs with matching owner should be deleted\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-D — CleanupManager cleans orphaned resources\n375: \n376: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager and a Sandbox object\n377: - **WHEN** cleanupOrphanedResources is called\n378: - **THEN** it should clean services, configmaps, and PVCs associated with the sandbox\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-E — CleanupManager finds orphaned services\n381: \n382: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n383: - **WHEN** FindOrphanedServices is called with namespace and sessionID\n384: - **THEN** it should return service names that have no owner references\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: AR-038-001-F — CleanupManager CleanupAllResources\n387: \n388: - **GIVEN** a CleanupManager with a Kubernetes client\n389: - **WHEN** CleanupAllResources is called with a sandbox\n390: - **THEN** it should clean all associated resources\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Feature: BatchManager Operations\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-A — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes synchronously under threshold\n397: \n398: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n399: - **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with fewer than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n400: - **THEN** it should delete all sandboxes synchronously\n401: - **AND** return a BatchDeleteResponse with deleted and failed counts\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: AR-038-002-B — BatchManager deletes all sandboxes asynchronously over threshold\n404: \n405: - **GIVEN** a BatchManager with workloadMgr and gracefulMgr\n406: - **WHEN** handleDeleteAllSandboxes is called with more than AsyncThreshold (10) sandboxes\n407: - **THEN** it should start async deletion in background\n408: - **AND** return immediately with all items marked as deleted\n409: \n\n(Showing lines 310-409 of 724. Use offset=410 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| `--port` | port | Optional[int] |\n| `--build-mode` | build_mode | Optional[str] |\n| `--description` | description | Optional[str] |\n| `--output` | (output path) | Optional[str] |\n\n---\n\n# Delta Spec: AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing Go unit tests for the workloadmanager module (`pkg/workloadmanager`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-038\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881424240,"end":1775881424255}}}}
